ubusercontent.com/u/77117846?v=4","status":"published","external_link":"https://www.twilio.com/blog/danger-js-helping-paste-focus","excerpt":"There’s always a checklist. Whether you’re writing code or reviewing it, every repo has a checklist of what should be included in a PR – and sometimes what shouldn’t. But what happens when that list becomes unwieldy as a project grows?...","machineDate":"2022-10-18"},{"title":"Paste Design System Newsletter - September 2022 Edition","slug":"/blog/2022-09-23-paste-newsletter/","date":"September 23, 2022","author":"Paste","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/t/3335688?s=280&v=4","author_link":null,"status":"published","external_link":null,"excerpt":"What's new in Paste in September 2022? NEW components, NEW icons, insights into our customer experience, and more!","machineDate":"2022-09-23"},{"title":"Paste Design System Newsletter - July 2022 Edition","slug":"/blog/2022-07-26-paste-newsletter/","date":"July 26, 2022","author":"Paste","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/t/3335688?s=280&v=4","author_link":null,"status":"published","external_link":null,"excerpt":"What's new in Paste in July 2022? New tokens list page, Figma Slot components, Chat Log documentation, and more!","machineDate":"2022-07-26"},{"title":"Paste Design System Newsletter - June 2022 Edition","slug":"/blog/2022-06-28-paste-newsletter/","date":"June 28, 2022","author":"Paste","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/t/3335688?s=280&v=4","author_link":null,"status":"published","external_link":null,"excerpt":"What's new in Paste in June 2022? Paste Intellisense, resizeable Textarea, important upgrades, and more!","machineDate":"2022-06-28"},{"title":"Bringing Cohesion to the Twilio Product Suite: Part I","slug":"/blog/2022-05-17-bringing-cohesion-to-the-twilio-product-suite-part-i/","date":"May 17, 2022","author":"Katie Porter","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5374045?v=4","author_link":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jane-k-porter/","status":"published","external_link":"https://www.twilio.com/blog/bringing-cohesion-to-the-twilio-product-suite-part-i","excerpt":"Learn about the research driving Twilio's work in creating a cohesive design language in order to pave the way for a unified product experience.","machineDate":"2022-05-17"},{"title":"Paste Design System Newsletter - April 2022 Edition","slug":"/blog/2022-04-06-paste-newsletter/","date":"April 6, 2022","author":"Paste","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/t/3335688?s=280&v=4","author_link":null,"status":"published","external_link":null,"excerpt":"What's new in Paste in April 2022? i18n, dark theme, badge component updates, data visualization, and more!","machineDate":"2022-04-06"},{"title":"Paste's Path to a Transparent Package Categorization System","description":"A brief outline detailing how Twilio's Design System previously categorized component and pattern packages and what sparked a change.","slug":"/blog/2021-07-26-pastes-path-to-a-transparent-package-categorization-system/","date":"July 26, 2021","author":"Nora Krantz","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/75342690?v=4","author_link":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/norakrantz/","status":"published","excerpt":"When integrating a library into a project, you’ll likely want to ensure that it’s a mature and well-maintained library that won’t be deprecated a month down the line. If your project is a customer-facing platform and the library maintains your frontend components, all the more reason to have trust. Transparency between the library and the consumer is integral to building that trust. Our previous...","machineDate":"2021-07-26"},{"title":"Insights & Metrics that Inform the Paste Design System","slug":"/blog/2021-04-29-insights-and-metrics-that-inform-the-paste-design-system/","date":"April 29, 2021","author":"Shadi Isber","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1592327?v=4","author_link":"https://twitter.com/thesisb","status":"published","external_link":"https://www.twilio.com/blog/insights-metrics-inform-paste-design-system","excerpt":"On Twilio's Paste design system team, we're often curious about who uses our work and how they use it. Besides being generally interesting, this information helps us track the adoption of our system, which helps clarify the business case of our work, while also informing us for our future decision making. This post will show you how we're tracking Paste's usage and how we use this data to improve...","machineDate":"2021-04-29"},{"title":"Growing Pains and How We Scaled our Design System Support","slug":"/blog/2020-11-26-growing-pains-and-how-we-scaled-our-design-system-support/","date":"November 26, 2020","author":"Aayush Iyer","avatar":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2206776?v=4","author_link":"https://twitter.com/aayush","status":"published","external_link":"https://aayush.fyi/writing/scaling_support","excerpt":"If you're building a new platform team, your customers are going to go through many changes. In the case of a design system, tools, hacks, and practices that made your team wildly successful are also the cause of long term design and technical debt. Making corrective changes to mitigate these problems with a platform can often mean taking away these...","machineDate":"2020-11-26"}],"navigationData":[{"Documentation":true,"status":"production","Feature":"Account Switcher","Component Category":"component","Figma":"yes","Code":"yes","Design committee review":"yes","Engineer committee review":"yes"},{"Documentation":true,"status":"production","Feature":"AI Chat Log","Component Category":"component","Figma":"yes","Design committee review":"yes","Engineer committee review":"yes"},{"Documentation":true,"status":"production","Feature":"Alert","Component Category":"component","Figma":"yes","Code":"yes","Design committee review":"yes","Engineer committee review":"yes"},{"Documentation":true,"status":"production","Feature":"Alert Dialog","Component Categ